Rahoton da aka fitar a wannan makon ya ce kungiyar, wacce aka fi sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP), ta danganta ta da kungiyar 'yan kishin Islama ta Afghanistan.
Wasu daga cikin 'ya'yan kungiyar TTP har sun shiga kungiyar IS wacce ke da hedkwatarta a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan ba ta mayar da martani a ranar Lahadi ga buƙatun da Associated Press ta yi don yin sharhi ba.
Rahoton ya ce kungiyar IS a Afghanistan, wacce aka fi sani da IS a lardin Khorasan, ta sha da kyar a hannun jami'an tsaron Afghanistan da sojojin Amurka da na NATO, har ma a wasu lokutan kungiyar Taliban ta Afghanistan.
Kungiyar masu sa ido kan nazari da takunkumi ta Amurka ce ta shirya rahoton, wacce ke bin diddigin kungiyoyin ta'addanci a duniya.
Rahoton ya kiyasta cewa mambobin kungiyar IS a Afghanistan sun kai 2,200, kuma yayin da shugabancinta ya ragu, IS har yanzu tana cikin shugabanninta wani dan kasar Siriya Abu Said Muhammad al-Khorasani.
Rahoton ya kuma ce tawagar masu sa ido sun samu bayanin cewa wasu manyan kwamandojin gwamnatin Musulunci biyu, Abu Qutaibah da Abu Hajar al-Iraqi, sun isa Afghanistan ne kwanan nan daga Gabas ta Tsakiya.
